Experimental and computational characterization of diffusion in bioprinting. A) Fluorescence imaging was used to characterize the diffusion of a rhodamine‐based dye through a crosslinked Pluronic F127‐diacrylate hydrogel. The spatial peak variance σ
2 was calculated based on fluorescence intensity profiles, while the diffusion coefficient was determined from the slope of σ
2 as a function of time. Reproduced with permission.[

